The size of the national debt of Italy increased to record levels
The size of Italy's public debt in June 2016 exceeded 2.248 trillion euros.
The country's central bank said that this amount is a historical maximum, RIA Novosti reports.
The previous negative record was set in May this year.
Then the size of the national debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that in the first half of the year, Italy's debt burden increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, Italy's public debt amounted to 132.7% of the country's GDP.
Meanwhile, Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pier Carlo Padoan predicted a decline in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 - to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport were received by 141 victims of the terrorist attack in Domodedovo.
141 people received charitable payments from the Aviatsionny Foundation, which was created by the management of the Domodedovo airport to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reports.
According to the press secretary of the airport Alexander Vlasov, two more applications are currently under consideration.
"The foundation continues charitable payments to the victims of the 2011 terrorist attack and provides comprehensive assistance in resolving existing issues," Vlasov added, recalling that a website of the foundation was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims, containing complete information on the procedure for providing charitable assistance.
In 2011, in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo, a suicide bomber detonated an explosive device.
As a result of the terrorist attack, 37 people were killed, another 172 were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years
An international group of biologists came to the conclusion that the longest-lived vertebrate animal is the Greenland polar shark, which can live for about 500 years, reports RT.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, whose length exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years old.
Biologists believe that an important role in the longevity of the shark is played by a low metabolism, which leads to slow development.
Female Greenland sharks only reach sexual maturity by the age of 150.
Previously, it was believed that the "neighbor" of the shark - the bowhead whale - lives the longest vertebrate.
The oldest individual known to scientists was slightly older than 210 years.
