Russia and Turkey: "Alliance of the Bad"?
It was the gesture that ended the crisis.
The leaders of Russia and Turkey met on Tuesday to shake hands and declare an official end to an eight-month war of words and economic sanctions.
But when Vladimir Putin greeted his Turkish counterpart in the gilded hall of a palace in St. Petersburg, I had a strong impression that Ankara wanted this reconciliation more.
