Moscow"Gazstroybank" was left without a license from the Central Bank.
On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia revoked the license to carry out banking operations from the credit organization Joint-Stock Commercial Bank "GAZSTROYBANK", registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC JSCB GAZSTROYBANK pursued a high-risk credit policy related to the placement of funds in low-quality assets.
An adequate assessment of the risks taken at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets led to the emergence of grounds for the credit institution to implement measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in conducting dubious transit operations.
A temporary administration has been appointed in the bank for a period of validity until the moment of appointment to the bankruptcy manager or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of the credit institution in accordance with federal laws are suspended.
JSCB "GAZSTROYBANK" is a member of the deposit insurance system.
Recall that the payment of insurance compensation to depositors of the bank, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On Insurance of Deposits of Individuals in Banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% of the balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles. in total per depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
