Fopp, which has now set aside almost the entire floor of vinyl, has a much more diverse audience when I arrive.
There are couples in their 70s, tourists taking pictures, teenage boys and middle-aged women.
While the atmosphere is less laid-back than in the aforementioned stores — Wild Beast's latest synth and sexy pop, rather than jazz improvisation, makes its way through the speakers — it's nice to see the variety in its customers.
