The Russian Copper Company (RCC) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that RCC undertook to modernize one of the oldest and most environmentally "dirty" enterprises in the country - the Karabash copper smelting plant.
Karabash Copper Smelter was founded by an English joint-stock company headed by Leslie Urquhart in 1910.
In Soviet times, it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country's economy, and it actually ensured the vital activity of the whole city.
However, in the 1990s, due to financial problems, production was stopped, which led to serious social problems in Karabash.
In 1998, it was decided to resume the work of the Karabash copper smelter.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabash plant - environmental.
By the early 2000s, Karabash was already notorious as an environmental disaster zone.
The situation at Karabashmedi began to change in 2004, after the company came under the management of the Russian Copper Company.
The company began to modernize production, which began to gradually reduce the environmental burden on the environment.
This was recently noted by the Governor of the Chelyabinsk region Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in early July.
The head of the South Urals called the grandiose changes that have occurred with the enterprise since Karabashmed moved to the RCC group.
The main measure for the modernization of Karabashmedi in recent years has been the construction of a new sulfuric acid workshop, which allows capturing up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the President of the Russian Copper Company Vsevolod Levin, the volume of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of CJSC "Karabashmed" is the reconstruction of the converter redistribution.
Replacement of three converters, sprayers, gas duct is scheduled for the end of 2017.
The cost of the project is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016, it is planned to launch a new workshop for the treatment of industrial effluents worth 1 billion rubles.
In turn, the amount of taxes deducted to the budget of the city of Karabash will also grow.
For the entire period of implementation of the Tominsky GOK project - from the beginning of construction to the commissioning of the second stage - the federal treasury will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the gok is put into operation, tax revenues to the budgets of all levels may amount to 80.9 billion rubles.
During the year of production in the Varna district, 346.3 million rubles were transferred to the budgets of different levels.
And that's for the first year.
"The longer the enterprise successfully operates, the more deductions can be," Valery Ulanovsky added.
The RCC clarified that in 2015 tax deductions from Mikheevsky GOK approached 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of RCC enterprises in the life and development of the territories of their presence is not limited to tax deductions.
RCC enterprises help to repair and maintain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, and improve territories.
In 2016, one of the largest social projects of the Russian Copper Company in Karabash was a major overhaul, and in fact - an almost complete reconstruction of kindergarten N9 for 95 pupils.
The building, built in 1960, was in disrepair.
Also on the territory of the RCC Arena there will be a landscape park with an artificial pond, underground and above-ground parking for 600 cars, cafes and sports shops.
"RCC Arena" will allow to hold spectacular professional sports events of international level.
But the main task of this project is to make physical education and sports in comfortable conditions accessible to residents of Chelyabinsk, primarily to children.
