The military of the Black Sea Fleet conducted a rehearsal of actions for anti-submarine and sabotage defense in the Black Sea.
This was reported to RIA Novosti by the representative of the press service of the Ministry of Defense for the Navy Igor Dygalo.
The training was conducted as part of the first stage of exercises on special types of support for the actions of the Navy forces.
"The servicemen of the anti-submarine and sabotage units worked out the anti-submarine and sabotage defense of the basing point of the fleet forces on the coast and the adjacent sea area of the Black Sea," Dygalo said.
About 400 servicemen, more than 10 units of military equipment, including Mi-8 and Ka-27 helicopters, Grachonok anti-sabotage boats and Raptor patrol boats, participated in the exercises.
During the maneuvers, the forces of the brandwachten ships using sonar means detected conditional sabotage groups and repelled the attack of "underwater saboteurs" from the sea on the basing point of the Black Sea Fleet forces.
An airborne assault group landed from the Ka-27 helicopter, which blocked and destroyed the saboteurs of the conditional enemy.
After that, the minesweepers of the Black Sea Fleet went to sea to search for mines.
Dygalo said that "these exercises of the Black Sea Fleet are carried out in accordance with the plan for the preparation and conduct of the upcoming command post exercise "Caucasus-2016" and the plan for the preparation of the Navy."
From July 18 to July 30, Ukraine and the United States held joint military exercises of the Sea Breeze 2016 fleets in the Black Sea.
In total, about four thousand people from 16 countries took part in the maneuvers.
More than 25 ships, boats and support vessels of the United States, Turkey, Romania and Ukraine were involved in the maritime component.
A court in the suburbs of Moscow arrested a father for the murder of an adopted daughter: Investigation and court: Law enforcement agencies: Lenta.ru
The Ozersk City Court of the Moscow Region authorized the arrest of Roman Chernikov, who confessed to the murder of his six-year-old adopted daughter.
On Thursday, August 11, as reported by the city news agency "Moscow", said the press secretary of the court Nina Zhilkina.
"The court granted the request of the investigating authorities to choose a preventive measure against Chernikov in the form of detention for two months," she said.
Chernikov will be under arrest until October 9.
On August 11, the Investigative Committee for the Moscow Region reported that the adoptive parents and grandmother of a six-year-old girl had confessed to her murder.
In particular, Roman Chernikov said that he committed the murder of a child on one of the days of April 2016 out of personal hostile relations, being at home in a state of alcoholic intoxication.
Then, in order to hide the child's body, he burned it and scattered the remains with his wife over a large area.
On the evening of August 9, during interrogation with the investigator, the adoptive parents reported that in April 2016, a six-year-old child had drowned in a bathtub.
For a long time, they managed to hide the disappearance of the girl from everyone, but in August, having learned that guardianship officers were soon to come to their home, they decided to tell everyone that the child was missing.
The parents stated that on August 6, their adopted daughter left the territory of the house where they lived as a family without permission and disappeared.
