Owners of instant messengers and mail services must identify users and remove prohibited information - this is the summary of the bill developed by the Media and Communication Union (ISS), which unites the largest Russian telecom operators (Vedomosti has).
Employees of the three member companies of the union confirmed that such a project is being discussed.
In early autumn, it should be presented to the working group led by First Deputy Prime Minister Igor Shuvalov, says the interlocutor of Vedomosti in the ISS.
We are talking about amendments to the laws on communications and on the media.
They provide that any "organizer of the dissemination of information on the Internet that provides the possibility of exchanging electronic messages" is obliged to identify users on the basis of information contained in the databases of telecom operators, having previously concluded contracts with them.
And also "immediately block messages or publications that contain information disseminated in violation of the requirements of Russian legislation."
Otherwise, operators have the right to restrict access to the service by the decision of Roskomnadzor.
