The Clinton campaign released tax returns until 2007.
The Clintons, who now live in Chappaqua, New York, paid an average federal tax rate of about 32 percent from 2007 to 2014 and an effective cumulative tax rate of about 40.5 percent.
The Clintons' 2015 declaration showed that, unlike most Americans, only $100 of their income was sourced from salaries.
