Notices for transport tax will no longer be sent by mail - the site Behind the wheel www.zr.ru
The tax inspectorate has changed the procedure for sending notifications of property taxes.
All Russian car owners are accustomed to the scheme that has not changed over the years: in summer and autumn they receive receipts by mail for the payment of transport tax for the previous year.
This year, however, many will not wait for them.
The fact is that the tax inspectorate has quietly changed the procedure for notifying citizens.
Those who are registered in the "Personal Account of the Taxpayer" on the official website of the department nalog.ru, notifications will come in electronic form.
The inspectorate automatically considered such Russians to be online users and crossed them out of the standard, "paper" mailing list.
The innovation will affect all owners of vehicles and real estate.
Everyone else will still receive the usual letters.
However, the opportunity to return to the old scheme is also available to account holders on the site.
To do this, they will have to visit the tax office during August and write an application.
On the one hand, the new order is more modern and convenient.
The notification will appear in the "personal account" immediately after compilation, while the letter will go on for several days and may be completely lost.
In addition, the number of users of the Internet service of the tax inspectorate has exceeded 18 million people, which will allow the department to seriously save on mailing.
On the other hand, the modest news on the inspection's website is clearly not enough to inform citizens about the changed order.
Some could register in the "personal account" to receive a one-time service and have long forgotten about it.
These people will not wait for notices by mail and, without knowing it, will fall into the category of defaulters with all the ensuing consequences.
Access to the "Taxpayer's Personal Account" is carried out in three ways: through the account of the portal gosuslugi.ru, using an electronic signature or entering the login and password specified in the registration card.
The latter can be obtained in person at any branch of the tax inspectorate (regardless of the place of registration).
We remind you that this year the transport tax must be paid before December 1.
Notifications began in July.
